body:
verilator version: Verilator 5.015 devel rev v5.014-31-g63db60f64
PS: this bug not happened at 5.012

code (partial):
```verilog
typedef struct {
    logic a;
} Data_t;
Data_t buffer[16];
........
// bug code
if (i_vld) begin
    if (buffer[idx].a) begin : bug_block // BUG: I set all buffer[x].a to constant 0
        // BUG: but it is still executed
        new_idx <= (idx == 15) ? 0 : idx + 1;
        $display("a %b : %h", buffer[idx].a, idx);
       // LOG: buffer[idx].a sometimes is 0 and sometimes is 1
       // but in the dumped wave， buffer[idx].a is always 0
    end
    else begin
        new_idx <= idx;
    end
end
........
```

I'm not sure what the cause of this bug
at verilator 5.012 has not this bug and bug_block is not be executed
(ps: verilator 5.012 i also find a bug that "lvalue required as left operand of assignment " in generated c++ code)
(what they have in common is member variables involving struct)
